# Plan mode — no shell workarounds

When **Plan mode** is active and file edits are blocked (Write/StrReplace rejected, or mode switch to Agent was declined):

1. **Stop** — do not implement code, config, or repo changes.
2. **Tell the user** to switch to **Agent mode** before continuing.
3. **Do not** route implementation through the shell (`cat`, heredocs, Python patch scripts, etc.) as a workaround. That bypasses review and is inconsistent with how Cursor expects work to happen.

## Allowed in Plan mode

- Read-only exploration (search, read files, explain design).
- Updating plan documents when the user is iterating on the plan.
- Answering questions.

## When the user explicitly asks to execute

If they clearly say implement / merge / ship / execute the plan, prefer **Agent mode**. If still blocked, ask them to switch modes — do not silently implement via shell.
